		<band height="142">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="142" uuid="1e378449-4b17-491d-b0cc-8cf5201c67f7"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[It should be considered that under some disease conditions, such as tumours, molecular features may not be present homogeneously in the tissue specimen or sample. Therefore, it is important that the part of actual tissue specimen or sample used for molecular examination is evaluated by a medically qualified pathologist. In this context it should be documented which features of a disease are actually reflected in the tissue specimen or sample used for molecular examination (e.g. different molecular mechanisms can be activated in the centre and at the invasion front of the tumour, also tumours can be composed of areas showing different differentiation grades).]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
